{"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Migrating to 1.19","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}]},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"There are no steps needed to migrate to 1.19 of the Composable Architecture, but there are a number","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of changes and improvements that have been made to the "},{"code":"Store","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that one should be aware of."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Store-internals-rewrite","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Store internals rewrite"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The store’s internals have been rewritten to improved performance and to pave the way for future","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"features. While this should not be a breaking change, with any rewrite it is important to thoroughly","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"test your application after upgrading.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"StateObject-compatibility","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"StateObject compatibility"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"type":"text","text":" allow a view to own a value or object over time, ensuring that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when a parent view is recomputed, the view-local state isn’t recreated from scratch."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"One important difference between ","type":"text"},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"@StateObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is that ","type":"text"},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"’s initializer is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"tex